OL,3,C'This is really unfair': King's Cross
OL,4,Cremoves train information early
OL,6,F"I can understand Network Rail
OL,7,Fthinking this is a good plan, but
OL,8,Fplease think about it from the
OL,9,Fpassengers' point of view. If you have
OL,10,Fjust emerged from the seven spirals of
OL,11,Fdespair of King's Cross underground
OL,12,Fand have three minutes to go, you know
OL,13,Fthat you should be able to make your
OL,14,Ftrain.
OL,16,F"Passengers will always find a
OL,17,Fworkaround, and several apps can tell
OL,18,Fyou what platform to go to. The
OL,19,Ftrouble is that checking the apps
OL,20,Fwhile running for your train is not
OL,21,Fgoing to be great. "
